DESCRIPTION : [PROJET FIN D'ANNEE SUR LE THEME D'IMAGE SATTELITE : Jeu de données d’images RVB dérivées de l’imagerie satellite Sentinel-2, conçu pour la classification des types de terrains et les applications de télédétection.Ce jeu de données comprend dix classes distinctes de couverture terrestre, ce qui le rend adapté aux modèles d’apprentissage automatique dans les domaines de la surveillance environnementale, de l’agriculture et de l’aménagement urbain.]¶

Le jeu de données couvre les types de terrains suivants :¶

Forêt : Zones densément boisées, incluant les forêts naturelles et les plantations.¶

Résidentiel : Régions urbaines et suburbaines comprenant des maisons, des bâtiments et des zones habitées.¶

Végétation herbacée : Prairies, arbustes et plantes non ligneuses.¶

Mer/Lac : Grandes masses d’eau, y compris les mers, lacs et océans.¶

Cultures annuelles : Terres agricoles avec des cultures plantées et récoltées au cours d’une seule année.¶

Industriel : Zones comportant des usines, entrepôts et installations de fabrication.¶

Rivière : Cours d’eau tels que les rivières et les ruisseaux.¶

Autoroute : Routes principales, autoroutes et voies de transport.¶

Cultures permanentes : Terres avec des cultures qui poussent de façon continue, telles que les vignobles et les vergers.¶

Pâturage : Prairies utilisées pour le pâturage du bétail.¶

import os
import shutil
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import random

random.seed(42)

# Chemin dossier source (images classées par sous-dossiers de classes)
base_dir = r"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\dataimagesattelite"

# Chemin dossier destination (où les dossiers train/val/test seront créés)
output_dir = r"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\EuroSAT_split"

# Ratios pour le split
train_ratio = 0.7
val_ratio = 0.15
test_ratio = 0.15

# Créer les dossiers train/val/test + sous dossiers classes
for split in ['train', 'val', 'test']:
    split_dir = os.path.join(output_dir, split)
    os.makedirs(split_dir, exist_ok=True)
    for class_name in os.listdir(base_dir):
        class_dir = os.path.join(split_dir, class_name)
        os.makedirs(class_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Pour chaque classe, lister les images et les répartir dans train/val/test
for class_name in os.listdir(base_dir):
    class_path = os.path.join(base_dir, class_name)
    if not os.path.isdir(class_path):
        continue
    images = [f for f in os.listdir(class_path) if f.lower().endswith(('.jpg', '.jpeg', '.png'))]
    random.shuffle(images)

    # Split train / temp (val+test)
    train_imgs, temp_imgs = train_test_split(images, test_size=(1 - train_ratio), random_state=42)
    # Split temp en val et test
    val_imgs, test_imgs = train_test_split(temp_imgs, test_size=test_ratio/(val_ratio + test_ratio), random_state=42)

    # Copier dans le dossier train
    for img in train_imgs:
        src = os.path.join(class_path, img)
        dst = os.path.join(output_dir, 'train', class_name, img)
        shutil.copy2(src, dst)

    # Copier dans le dossier val
    for img in val_imgs:
        src = os.path.join(class_path, img)
        dst = os.path.join(output_dir, 'val', class_name, img)
        shutil.copy2(src, dst)

    # Copier dans le dossier test
    for img in test_imgs:
        src = os.path.join(class_path, img)
        dst = os.path.join(output_dir, 'test', class_name, img)
        shutil.copy2(src, dst)

    print(f"{class_name}: train={len(train_imgs)}, val={len(val_imgs)}, test={len(test_imgs)}")

print("✅ Répartition train/val/test terminée.")

# Data augmentation uniquement pour train

    preprocessing_function=preprocess_input,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True
)

# Pas d'augmentation pour val et test, juste préprocessing
val_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input)
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    r"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\EuroSAT_split\train",
    target_size=img_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode='sparse',
    shuffle=True
)

    r"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\EuroSAT_split\val",
    target_size=img_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode='sparse',
    shuffle=False
)

test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    r"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\EuroSAT_split\test",
    target_size=img_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode='sparse',

)

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from collections import Counter
from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight

def analyze_class_distribution_from_generator(generator):
    # Récupérer tous les labels générés
    y_labels = generator.classes  # np.array déjà encodé

    counter = Counter(y_labels)
    total = len(y_labels)

    print("📊 Distribution des classes :")
    for label, count in sorted(counter.items()):
        pourcentage = (count / total) * 100
        print(f"Classe {label} : {count} exemples ({pourcentage:.2f}%)")

    # Afficher le graphique
    plt.bar(counter.keys(), counter.values())
    plt.xlabel("Classe")
    plt.ylabel("Nombre d'exemples")
    plt.title("Distribution des classes dans le dossier train")
    plt.xticks(ticks=list(counter.keys()), labels=list(generator.class_indices.keys()), rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # Calcul automatique des poids
    classes = np.unique(y_labels)
    class_weights = compute_class_weight(class_weight='balanced', classes=classes, y=y_labels)
    class_weight_dict = dict(zip(classes, class_weights))

    print("\n⚖️  Class Weights (à utiliser dans model.fit):")
    print(class_weight_dict)

    return class_weight_dict

PREMIER MODEL (VGG16)¶

from tensorflow.keras.applications import VGG16
model_VGG16 = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(128,128,3))

for layer in model_VGG16.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

model_VGG16 = Sequential([
    model_VGG16,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l1(0.01)),
    layers.Dropout(0.2),
    layers.Dense(224, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.01)),
    layers.Dropout(0.3),
    layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

model_VGG16.summary()

from tensorflow.keras.applications import EfficientNetB3

model_EfficienNetB3 = EfficientNetB3(weights='imagenet', include_top=False,input_shape=(128,128,3))

for layer in model_EfficienNetB3.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

model_EfficienNetB3 = Sequential([
    model_EfficienNetB3,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(600, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l1(0.01)),
    layers.Dropout(0.3),
    layers.Dense(550, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(224, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.01)),
    layers.Dropout(0.2),
    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])
model_EfficienNetB3.summary()

TROIXIEME MODEL (RESNET50)¶

In [ ]:
from tensorflow.keras.applications import ResNet50

model_ResNet50 = ResNet50(weights='imagenet', include_top=False,input_shape=(128,128,3))

for layer in model_ResNet50.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

model_ResNet50 = Sequential([
    model_ResNet50,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'),                
    layers.Dropout(0.4),
    layers.Dense(896, activation='relu'),                 
    layers.Dense(768, activation='relu'),                 
    layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.01)),
    layers.Dropout(0.4),
    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l1(0.01)),
    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax') 
])
model_ResNet50.summary()

from tensorflow.keras.applications import DenseNet121

model_DenseNet121 = DenseNet121(weights='imagenet', include_top=False,input_shape=(128,128,3))

for layer in model_DenseNet121.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

model_DenseNet121 = Sequential([
    model_DenseNet121,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'),
    layers.BatchNormalization(),
    layers.Dropout(0.3),

    layers.Dense(768, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.01)),
    layers.BatchNormalization(),
    layers.Dropout(0.4),

    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    layers.BatchNormalization(),
    layers.Dropout(0.3),

    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l1(0.01)),
    layers.BatchNormalization(),
    layers.Dropout(0.2),

    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    layers.BatchNormalization(),

    layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')  
])
model_DenseNet121.summary()

DERNIER MODEL (cnn)¶

In [ ]:
# Architecture CNN 
model_cnn = Sequential([
    # Bloc 1
    Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(128, 128, 3)),
    BatchNormalization(),
    MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),

    # Bloc 2
    Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    BatchNormalization(),
    MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),

    # Bloc 3
    Conv2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    BatchNormalization(),
    MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),

    # Flatten + Dense layers
    Flatten(),
    Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.3),
    Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.3),
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')  # 10 classes
])

# Compilation
model_cnn.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0005),
    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

model_cnn.summary()
